#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:22
msgid ""
"The Transform tool lets you quickly transform the current selection or "
"layer. Basic transformation options include resize, rotate and skew. In "
"addition, you have the option to apply advanced transforms such as "
"Perspective, Warp, Cage and Liquid. These are all powerful options and will "
"give you complete control over your selections/layers."
msgstr ""
"変形ツールは選択部分やレイヤーを素早く変形させることができます。基本的な変形"
"とは拡大縮小、回転やゆがませることです。それに加えてパースグリッド、格子点、"
"ケージやゆがみがあります。どれも強力なオプションで選択やレイヤーについて自由"
"な操作ができるでしょう。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:24
msgid ""
"When you first invoke the tool,  handles will appear at the corners and "
"sides, which you can use to resize your selection or layer. You can perform "
"rotations by moving the mouse above or to the left of the handles and "
"dragging it. You can also click anywhere inside the selection or layer and "
"move it by dragging the mouse."
msgstr ""
"最初にツールを呼び出すと角と縁にハンドルが現れ、レイヤーや選択を拡大縮小する"
"のに使えます。マウスをハンドルの上か左に持っていきドラッグすることで回転しま"
"す。また選択やレイヤー内部のどこでもマウスドラッグすることで移動することがで"
"きます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:26
msgid ""
"You can fine-tune the transform tool parameters using tool options docker. "
"The parameters are split between five tabs: Free Transform, Warp, "
"Perspective, Cage and Liquify."
msgstr ""
"ツールのオプションドッカーでは変形ツールのパラメーターをより詳細に調節できま"
"す。パラメーターは5つのタブに分かれています: 自由変形、パース、格子点、ケー"
"ジ、ゆがみです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:30
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Transform_Tool_Options.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:30
msgid "Free Transform docker."
msgstr "自由変形ドッカー。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:33
msgid "Free transform"
msgstr "自由変形"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:35
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "This allows you to do basic rotation, resizing, flipping, and even "
#| "perspective skewing if you hold the :kbd:`Ctrl` key. Holding "
#| "the :kbd:`Shift` key will maintain your aspect ratio throughout the "
#| "transform."
msgid ""
"This allows you to do basic rotation, resizing, flipping, and even "
"perspective skewing if you hold the :kbd:`Ctrl` key. Holding "
"the :kbd:`Shift` key will maintain your aspect ratio throughout the "
"transform. When you move the center pivot point, pressing :kbd:`Alt` will "
"allow you to limit it to the transformation bounds."
msgstr ""
"基本的な回転、リサイズ、反転や、:kbd:`Ctrl` キーを使えばパース状にゆがませる"
"ことができます。:kbd:`Shift` キーを押すことで変形の最中にアスペクト比を維持で"
"きます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:40
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_free.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:40
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:77
msgid "Free transform in action."
msgstr "自由変形を使ってみたところ。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:42
msgid ""
"If you look at the bottom, there are quick buttons for flipping "
"horizontally, vertically and rotating 90 degrees left and right. "
"Furthermore, the button to the left of the anchor point widget allows you to "
"choose whether to always transform using the anchor point, or not."
msgstr ""
"一番下には水平/垂直反転、左や右へ90度回転のクイックボタンがあります。さらに、"
"アンカーポイントウィジェット左にあるボタンでは常にアンカーポイントを使用して"
"変形するかを決めることができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:44
msgid ""
"`Video of how to use the anchor point for resizing. <https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v=grzccBVd0O8>`_"
msgstr ""
"`アンカーポイントを使ってリサイズする説明のビデオです。 <https://"
"www.youtube.com/watch?v=grzccBVd0O8>`_"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:47
msgid "Rotating the Transformation Bounds"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:49
msgid ""
"It is possible to rotate the visual transformation bounds without "
"transforming the image itself. This is particularly useful when dealing with "
"sections of an image that were drawn diagonally, like for example, a stick "
"at an angle."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:51
msgid ""
"By pressing :kbd:`Ctrl + Alt` before trying to rotate, the cursor will "
"switch to a bounds-rotation cursor, at which point a |mouseleft| + drag will "
"rotate the visual bounds. Then, releasing the keys, a regular transformation "
"can be performed. By rotating the transformation bounds to the actual image "
"being transformed, it can be easier to transform the image afterwards, "
"especially when aligning at a certain angle."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:56
msgid "Perspective"
msgstr "パースグリッド"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:58
msgid ""
"While free transform has some perspective options, the perspective transform "
"allows for maximum control. You can drag the corner points, or even the "
"designated vanishing point."
msgstr ""
"自由変形でも多少のパース操作はできますが、パースグリッド変形はすべての操作が"
"できます。角か消失点をドラッグします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:60
msgid ""
"You can also change the size, shear and position transform while remaining "
"in perspective with the tool-options."
msgstr ""
"ツールのオプションでパースグリッドを選択しながらでもサイズ、平行変形や位置の"
"変更ができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:64
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_perspective.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:64
msgid "Perspective transform."
msgstr "パースグリッド変形。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:69
msgid ""
"Warp allows you to deform the image by dragging from a grid or choosing the "
"dragging points yourself."
msgstr ""
"格子点はグリッドや自分で決めたドラッグポイントから画像を変形することができま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:73
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Transform_Tool_Options_Warp.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:73
msgid "Warp Option."
msgstr "格子点オプション。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:77
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_warp.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:79
msgid ""
"There are warp options: Rigid, Affine and Similitude. These change the "
"algorithm used to determine the strength of the deformation. The flexibility "
"determines, how strong the effect of moving these points are."
msgstr ""
"格子点にはオプションがあります: 固定、アフィンと相似です。これで変形の強さを"
"決めるアルゴリズムが変わります。柔軟さでポイントを移動したときの強さが決まり"
"ます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:82
msgid "Anchor Points"
msgstr "アンカーポイント"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:84
msgid "You can divide these either by subdivision or drawing custom points."
msgstr "分割で分けるかカスタムポイントを設定できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:86
msgid "Subdivision"
msgstr "分割"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:87
msgid "This allows you to subdivide the selected area into a grid."
msgstr "選択されたエリアをグリッドに分割します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:89
msgid "Draw"
msgstr "描画"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:89
msgid ""
"Draw the anchor points yourself. Locking the points will put you in "
"transform mode. Unlocking the points back into edit mode."
msgstr ""
"自分でアンカーポイントを描きます。ロックすると変形モードになり、ロック解除す"
"ると再度編集モードになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:94
msgid ""
"Create a cage around an image, and when it's closed, you can use it to "
"deform the image. If you have at least 3 points on the canvas, you can "
"choose to switch between deforming and editing the existing points."
msgstr ""
"画像の周りに囲いを作り、閉じると画像を変形するものとして使えます。最低3つのア"
"ンカーポイントがキャンバス上にあれば、変形するか既存のポイントを編集するか切"
"り替えられるようになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:98
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_cage.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:98
msgid "Transforming a straight banana to be curved with the cage tool."
msgstr "ケージツールで真っすぐなバナナを曲げる。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:101
msgid "Adjust Granularity"
msgstr "粒度の調整"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:105
msgid ""
"This adjusts the precision of the cage transform grid. The lower the value, "
"the higher the quality of the transformation (and consequently, the lower "
"the speed). When the granularity is too high, the result starts to look "
"\"blocky\"."
msgstr ""
"ケージ変形ツールの正確さを調節します。値を低くすれば、変形の品質は高くなり(そ"
"して同時に、速度は落ち)ます。値が高すぎると、結果は少し\"ブロック状\"になりま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:107
msgid "Preview"
msgstr "プレビュー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:108
msgid ""
"Adjusts the granularity of the preview. It is recommended to have this "
"higher than the :guilabel:`Real` value, as it speeds up adjusting."
msgstr ""
"プレビューの粒度を調節します。速度向上の調整のため、ここの値は :guilabel:`リ"
"アル` より高いものであることが推奨されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:110
msgid "Real"
msgstr "リアル"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:110
msgid "Adjusts the granularity of the final result."
msgstr "粒度を最終的な作品に調整します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:113
msgid "Hotkeys"
msgstr "ホットキー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:115
msgid ""
"Both Cage and Warp use little nodes. These nodes can be selected and "
"deselected together by pressing the :kbd:`Ctrl` key before clicking nodes."
msgstr ""
"ケージと格子点はどちらも多くの点を使用しません。これらをまとめて選択したり選"
"択解除するには点をクリックする前に :kbd:`Ctrl` キーを押します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:117
msgid ""
"Then you can move them by pressing the cursor inside the bounding box. "
"Rotating is done by pressing and dragging the cursor outside the bounding "
"box and scaling the same, only one presses the :kbd:`Ctrl` key before doing "
"the motion."
msgstr ""
"そしてそのままバウンディングボックスの中にカーソルを動かします。バウンディン"
"グボックスの外で押しながらドラッグすることで回転ができ、拡大縮小も同様"
"に :kbd:`Ctrl` キーを一回押すだけです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:125
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Transform_Tool_Options_Liquify.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:126
msgid ""
"Like our deform brush, the liquify brush allows you to draw the deformations "
"straight on the canvas."
msgstr ""
"変形ブラシと同じように、ゆがみもキャンバス上に直接変形を描くことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:128
msgid "Move"
msgstr "移動"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:129
msgid "Drag the image along the brush stroke."
msgstr "ブラシストロークに合わせて画像をゆがませます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:130
msgid "Scale"
msgstr "サイズ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:131
msgid "Grow/Shrink the image under the cursor."
msgstr "カーソルの下で画像を拡大/縮小します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:132
msgid "Rotate"
msgstr "回転"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:133
msgid "Twirl the image under the cursor."
msgstr "カーソル下の画像を回転させます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:134
msgid "Offset"
msgstr "オフセット"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:135
msgid "Shift the image under the cursor."
msgstr "カーソル下の画像をずらします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:137
msgid "Undo"
msgstr "取り消し"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:137
msgid "Erases the actions of other tools."
msgstr "他のツールで行った操作を取り消します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:141
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_liquefy.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:141
msgid "Liquify used to turn an apple into a pear."
msgstr "リンゴを梨にゆがませたところ。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:143
msgid "In the options for each brush there are:"
msgstr "それぞれのブラシについてのオプションは:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:145
msgid "Mode"
msgstr "モード"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:146
msgid ""
"This is either :guilabel:`Wash` or :guilabel:`Build up`. :guilabel:`Wash` "
"will normalize the effect to be between none, and the amount parameter as "
"maximum. :guilabel:`Build up` will just add on until it's impossible."
msgstr ""
"これは :guilabel:`水彩` か :guilabel:`厚塗り` です。:guilabel:`水彩` は何もな"
"いところとのエフェクトを標準化し、パラメーターの値は最大です。:guilabel:`厚塗"
"り` はできなくなるまでただ追加していきます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:147
msgid "Size"
msgstr "サイズ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:148
msgid ""
"The brush size. The button to the right allows you to let it scale with "
"pressure."
msgstr "ブラシのサイズです。右のボタンで筆圧に対応させることもできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:149
msgid "Amount"
msgstr "量"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:150
msgid ""
"The strength of the brush. The button to the right lets it scale with tablet "
"pressure."
msgstr "ブラシの強さです。右のボタンで筆圧に対応させることもできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:151
msgid "Flow"
msgstr "流量"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:152
msgid "Only applicable with :guilabel:`Build up`."
msgstr ":guilabel:`厚塗り` でのみ利用します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:153
msgid "Spacing"
msgstr "描点間隔"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:154
msgid "The spacing of the liquify dabs."
msgstr "ゆがみ描点の距離です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:156
msgid "Reverse"
msgstr "反転"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:156
msgid ""
"Reverses the action, so grow becomes shrink, rotate results in clockwise "
"becoming counter-clockwise."
msgstr ""
"動作を反転しますので、拡大するものは縮小に、時計回りに回転するものは反時計回"
"りになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:160
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_deformvsliquefy.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:160
msgid "Liquify on the left and deform brush on the right."
msgstr "左はゆがみで右は変形ブラシ。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:162
msgid ""
"Krita also has a :ref:`deform_brush_engine` which is much faster than "
"liquify, but has less quality. If you are attempting to make liquify a "
"little faster, note that it speeds up with the less information it needs to "
"process, so working with liquify within a selection or using liquify on a "
"separate layer with little on it will greatly enhance the speed."
msgstr ""
"Krita にはまた :ref:`deform_brush_engine` があり、ゆがみよりも高速に動作しま"
"すが品質は劣ります。もしゆがみを高速にしたい場合は、処理に必要な情報を削る必"
"要があるので、物が少ないレイヤーに分けるか選択の中であればかなりの速度向上が"
"望めます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:171
msgid ""
"The mesh transform is similar to the warp and the cage transform, except "
"that its interface uses patches comprised of Bezier curve segments. This "
"transform mode is particularly useful for placing images and textures on "
"curved surfaces:"
msgstr ""
"メッシュ変形は格子点やケージ変形と似ていますが、ベジェ曲線に基づいて操作を行"
"う点が異なります。この変形モードは曲線上に画像やテクスチャを置く際にとても有"
"用です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:175
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_mesh.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:175
msgid ""
"Curving a logo to an apple with the mesh transform, with the control points "
"shown."
msgstr ""
"ハンドルを表示した状態で、メッシュ変形を使ってロゴをリンゴに合わせてゆがませ"
"ているところ。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:177
msgid ""
"This is a very keyboard shortcut heavy transform mode. When you start the "
"transform you will see the overlay, which consists of several nodes that can "
"be dragged around. You can drag on the segments between the nodes to curve "
"them precisely, or drag on patches themselves to freely transform "
"them. :kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` shortcut on nodes and "
"segments will allow you to subdivide the mesh. For more precision, enable "
"the control points in the tool options, so each Bezier segment can be fine-"
"tuned to your content."
msgstr ""
"この変形モードには多くのショートカットがあります。変形をするとドラッグできる"
"ノードが表示されます。このノード間にあるセグメントをドラッグしてやりたいよう"
"にカーブさせるか、パッチ自体をドラッグして自由に変形できます。:kbd:`Ctrl + "
"Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` ショートカットをノードやセグメントに行う"
"ことでメッシュの分割ができます。より正確にするには、ツールのオプションからア"
"ンカーポイントを有効にすればベジェ曲線の調節が可能になります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:179
msgid ""
"To assist in maintaining the curvature of a mesh, this tool has a concept of "
"'locked' transform. This mode is signalled by the lock icon in the cursor, "
"and on by default. When this is enabled, adjusting one segment will also "
"adjust its neighbouring segment in another patch. You can press :kbd:`Shift` "
"key while dragging a segment or control point to turn this feature off, "
"allowing for sharp angles in the mesh. After a sharp angle has been created, "
"the locked mode will try to keep this as well."
msgstr ""
"メッシュの曲率を維持したいなら、このツールには'ロック'変形の考え方がありま"
"す。このモードはカーソルのロックアイコンで示され、既定ではオンになっていま"
"す。これが有効になっていると、1つのセグメントを調整すると他のセグメントも同様"
"に調節されます。セグメントやアンカーポイントをドラッグしながら :kbd:`Shift` "
"キーを押すことでこの機能をオフにでき、メッシュでシャープな角度を作ることがで"
"きます。シャープな角度を作れたら、ロックモードはこの状態を維持しようとしま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:182
msgid "Shortcuts"
msgstr "ショートカット"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:184
msgid "Node or control point move"
msgstr "ノードや操作点の移動"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:185
msgid ""
"|mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` any of the round points. The big ones are the "
"'nodes' which determine the corners of a patch, and the small ones are the "
"'control points', which determine the curvature for their associated segment."
msgstr ""
"丸い点で |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。大きいものは'ノード'と言い画像"
"の角を決め、小さいものは'アンカーポイント'で関連する曲率を決めます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:186
msgid "Unlocked node or control point move"
msgstr "ロック解除されたノードやアンカーポイントの移動"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:187
msgid ":kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on a node or control point."
msgstr ""
"ノードやポイントで :kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:188
msgid "Locked segment move:"
msgstr "ロックされたセグメントの移動:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:189
msgid ""
"|mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on a segment. As explained above, this will adjust "
"neighbouring segments as well, to keep the curvature of the node intact."
msgstr ""
"セグメント上で |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。上で説明した通り、隣り合"
"う他のセグメントもノードに関わる曲率を維持しながら調節します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:190
msgid "Segment move"
msgstr "セグメントの移動"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:191
msgid ":kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on a segment of the mesh."
msgstr ""
"メッシュのセグメント上で :kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` しま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:192
msgid "Free patch deform:"
msgstr "自由な変形:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:193
msgid ""
"|mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on an empty area inside the mesh. This will allow "
"you to intuitively adjust a segment by just clicking anywhere and dragging. "
"The whole segment will then adjust all its control points around the point "
"of the cursor."
msgstr ""
"メッシュ内の何もないところで |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。またこれで"
"直感的にどこでもドラッグしてセグメントの調節ができます。カーソル周りにある操"
"作点すべてから全体を調節します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:195
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on a border segment to split "
"the mesh"
msgstr ""
"メッシュを分割するには縁のセグメント上で :kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |"
"mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:196
msgid "Split mesh or Move/Delete split:"
msgstr "メッシュの分割やその移動/削除:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:196
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on a node to change the split"
msgstr ""
"ノード上で :kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` することで分割の"
"変更をします"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:197
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` away a node to remove the split"
msgstr ""
"ノードを :kbd:`Ctrl + Alt +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` して離すことで分割"
"を削除します"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:198
msgid "Select multiple nodes"
msgstr "複数ノードを選択"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:199
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl +` |mouseleft| on a node or control or segment, these can then be "
"moved"
msgstr ""
"ノードやアンカーポイント、セグメント上で :kbd:`Ctrl +` |mouseleft| することで"
"移動できます"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:200
msgid "Move selection or mesh"
msgstr "選択やメッシュを移動"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:201
msgid ""
":kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on empty area outside the mesh."
msgstr ""
"メッシュ外の空白部分で :kbd:`Shift +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:202
msgid "Rotate selection or mesh"
msgstr "選択やメッシュを回転"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:203
msgid ""
"|mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on an empty area outside the mesh, if there is a "
"selection of nodes, it will rotate only them, otherwise the whole mesh will "
"be rotated."
msgstr ""
"メッシュ外の空白部分で |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。ノードの選択があ"
"ればそれだけが回転し、でなければメッシュ全体が回転します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:205
msgid "Scale selection or mesh"
msgstr "選択やメッシュの拡大縮小"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:205
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on empty area outside the mesh, if "
"there is a selection of nodes, it will scale only them, otherwise the whole "
"mesh will be scaled."
msgstr ""
"メッシュ外の空白部分で :kbd:`Ctrl +` |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ ドラッグ` します。"
"ノードの選択があればそれだけが拡大縮小し、でなければメッシュ全体が拡大縮小し"
"ます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:208
msgid "Tool options"
msgstr "ツールのオプション"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:209
msgid "Mesh Size"
msgstr "メッシュサイズ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:210
msgid ""
"Gives precise controls to change the amount of patches vertically and "
"horizontally. When increasing or decreasing the amount of patches, Krita "
"will try to keep the curvature the same, which can be used to your advantage."
msgstr ""
"パッチ量の垂直/水平方向での正確な操作ができます。パッチ量を上げたり下げたりす"
"ると、Krita は曲率をできるだけ維持しようとします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:212
msgid "This will toggle the control points."
msgstr "アンカーポイントのオンオフを切り替えます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:213
msgid "Show control points"
msgstr "アンカーポイントを表示"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:216
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Transformation Masks"
msgid "Transform Multiple Layers"
msgstr "変形マスク"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:218
msgid "Krita allows you to transform multiple layers at once."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:220
msgid ""
"In Krita versions older than 5.0 this required using "
"the :guilabel:`Recursive Transform` option while transforming a group layer, "
"whose icon was a little spider. Since 5.0, this option is enabled by default "
"for group layers (To achieve non-recursive transformation you can use the "
"layer lock feature)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:224
msgid ""
"Transforming multiple layers doesn't require a group anymore, now all layers "
"selected in the layer docker will be transformed at once."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:228
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Krita_transforms_recursive.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:228
msgid ""
"Krita allows you to transforms all the layers in the group, so with this "
"apple, both the lineart as the fill will be transformed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:231
msgid "Continuous Transform"
msgstr "連続変形"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:233
msgid ""
"If you apply a transformation, and try to start a new one directly "
"afterwards, Krita will attempt to recall the previous transform, so you can "
"continue it. This is a *continuous transform*. You can press the :kbd:`Esc` "
"key to cancel this and start a new transform, or press :guilabel:`Reset` in "
"the tool options while no transform is active."
msgstr ""
"変形を適用して、直後に新しい変形を直接行おうとすると、Krita は前回の変形を記"
"憶し繰り返しできるようにします。これが *連続変形* です。:kbd:`Esc` キーでキャ"
"ンセルし新しい変形を始めるか、何も変形がアクティブでない時にツールのオプショ"
"ンから :guilabel:`リセット` を押します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:236
msgid "Transformation Masks"
msgstr "変形マスク"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/transform.rst:238
msgid ""
"These allow you to make non-destructive transforms, check :ref:`here "
"<transformation_masks>` for more info."
msgstr ""
"これは非破壊での変形をすることができます。詳しくは :ref:`ここ "
"<transformation_masks>` を見てください。"

